JOHANNESBURG - Load shedding, high unemployment rates, waning infrastructure, and failing state-owned enterprises are just some of the talking points South Africans expect to be addressed in Wednesday's budget speech. Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana will address the nation with the annual budget speech at 2pm on Wednesday. In the lead-up to Godongwana's address, watch Refilwe Moloto and her guests delve into this year's finances below. 